The paper discusses the properties of local processors in biological and artificial neural systems, which suggests that it could belong to the sub-category of cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing). The paper also uses recent advances in information theory to study the properties of these processors, which suggests that it could belong to the sub-category of cs.IT (Information Theory). The paper discusses the information processing properties of contextual modulation, which suggests that it could belong to the sub-category of cs.LG (Learning). The paper also discusses the design of context-sensitive machine learning algorithms, which suggests that it could belong to the sub-category of cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence). Finally, the paper discusses the potential application of its findings to empirical neurobiological and psychophysical data, which suggests that it could belong to the sub-category of cs.SY (Systems and Control).
